==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inconsolable
<hw>In`con*sol"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inconsolabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>inconsolable</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Console</er>.]</ety> <def>Not consolable;
incapable of being consoled; grieved beyond susceptibility of comfort;
disconsolate.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With <qex>inconsolable</qex> distress she griev'd,⟦br⟧
And from her cheek the rose of beauty fled.</q>
<rj><qau>Falconer.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>In`con*sol"a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>In`con*sol"a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms></p>

